==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Succade
<hw>Suc"cade</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>succus</ets>, <ets>sucus</ets>, juice: cf. F. <ets>succade</ets> a
sugarbox. Cf. <er>Sucket</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
sweetmeat.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>Sweetmeats, or
preserves in sugar, whether fruit, vegetables, or confections.</def>
<rj><au>Blakely.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Succade gourd</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>Same as
<cref>Vegetable marrow</cref>, under <er>Vegetable</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succedane</ent>⟦br⟧
